 University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill Previous academic administrative positions held by at Calvin M. Boardman at the David Eccles School of Business include Finance Department Chairperson, Associate Dean and Acting Dean. Boardman earned his MBA from the University of Texas at Arlington and his Ph. from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill in Finance. Boardman is the author of two books, including Foundations of Business Thought (4th Edition. Boardman is the recipient of several awards including The University Professor Award, 1993, the Associated Students of the University of Utah Students Choice Award and the Marvin J. In 1996, he was awarded the Presidential Teaching Scholar Award, and in 1997, the David Eccles School of Business Distinguished Service Award. 